[size=18pt][b][color=#f39c12]Byzantine Fault Tolerance & Slashing[/color][/b][/size]

Q-NarwhalKnight's DAG-Knight consensus provides:

[list]
[li][b]Safety Guarantee[/b]: n ≥ 3f + 1 validators (tolerating f Byzantine faults)[/li]
[li][b]Finality[/b]: Sub-3-second deterministic finality[/li]
[li][b]Zero-Message Complexity[/b]: Anchor election via VDF proofs[/li]
[/list]

[b]Slashing Severity Tiers:[/b]

[table]
[tr][td][b]Offense[/b][/td][td][b]Slash %[/b][/td][td][b]Cooldown[/b][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Double-signing at same height[/td][td]100%[/td][td]Permanent ban[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Double-voting in consensus round[/td][td]50%[/td][td]30 days[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Extended downtime (>24h)[/td][td]1%[/td][td]7 days[/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Invalid block proposal[/td][td]5%[/td][td]14 days[/td][/tr]
[/table]

[b]Equivocation Proof Structure:[/b]
[code]
EquivocationProof {
    validator_id: [u8; 32],
    message_1: SignedMessage,
    message_2: SignedMessage,
    proof_type: DoubleSign | DoubleVote,
    timestamp: u64,
}
[/code]

[url=https://quillon.xyz/downloads/qnk-bft-slashing-whitepaper.pdf][b]BFT & Slashing Whitepaper[/b][/url]

