[size=18pt][b][color=#1abc9c]Integrated VM and Quantum DEX[/color][/b][/size]

The Q-VM (Q-NarwhalKnight Virtual Machine) and Quantum DEX share unified state:

[b]VM Features:[/b]
[list]
[li]Stack-based architecture with 256-bit word size[/li]
[li]Deterministic gas metering[/li]
[li]Native post-quantum signature verification opcodes[/li]
[li]Atomic state transitions with DEX pools[/li]
[/list]

[b]Quantum DEX Features:[/b]
[list]
[li]Physics-inspired AMM with golden ratio optimization[/li]
[li]Uncertainty-based pricing (Heisenberg model)[/li]
[li]Private liquidity pools[/li]
[li]MEV-resistant transaction ordering[/li]
[/list]

[b]Pricing Formula:[/b]
[code]
price = base_price × (1 + φ × volatility_factor) × uncertainty_premium

Where:
- φ = 1.618... (golden ratio)
- volatility_factor = σ(recent_trades)
- uncertainty_premium = quantum_state_contribution
[/code]

