[size=18pt][b][color=#9b59b6]v1.3.11-beta: TurboSync Fix[/color][/b][/size]

[b]Root Cause Identified:[/b] Two competing sync systems were sending block requests simultaneously.

[b]The Problem:[/b]
[code]
1. TurboSync (correct) → request_blocks_batch_async → pending_block_requests ✓
2. Legacy sync (wrong) → request_blocks_from_peer → outstanding_sync_requests ✗

Response handler looks in pending_block_requests
→ Legacy requests never match
→ "NO MATCHING REQUEST" warnings
→ Sync falls back to slow HTTP (1.6 blocks/sec)
[/code]

[b]The Fix:[/b]
Disabled all competing sync code paths:
[list]
[li][color=#2ecc71]✓[/color] Disabled GAP FILL sync (was calling request_blocks_from_peer)[/li]
[li][color=#2ecc71]✓[/color] Disabled DISCOVERY sync (was testing peers with wrong function)[/li]
[li][color=#2ecc71]✓[/color] Disabled FAST SYNC parallel requests[/li]
[li][color=#2ecc71]✓[/color] Disabled check_and_sync_blocks loop[/li]
[/list]

[b]Result:[/b] Only TurboSync (sync_to_height) now handles synchronization with proper channel-based response delivery.

[b]Expected Performance:[/b]
[list]
[li]P2P sync: ~100+ blocks/second[/li]
[li]HTTP fallback (last resort): ~1.6 blocks/second[/li]
[/list]

